parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to potential injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident. The stuck buckle can also cause damage to the door and surrounding components.
symptoms: The seatbelt fails to retract properly
the buckle gets caught in the door
the buckle is broken
the seatbelt buckle will not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right side brake caliper can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes straight to the floor with no braking effect
the brake pad is lying on the ground
a squeaking noise is heard prior to the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause sudden acceleration or failure to decelerate, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stuck down
the vehicle accelerates suddenly without input
the vehicle fails to decelerate when the accelerator pedal is released
the accelerator pedal requires repeated stomping or braking to loosen it.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective accelerator pedal assembly can cause the pedal to stick, leading to sudden acceleration or failure to decelerate, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stuck down
the vehicle accelerates suddenly without input
the vehicle fails to decelerate when the accelerator pedal is released
the accelerator pedal requires repeated stomping or braking to loosen it.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A rusted and leaking fuel tank can cause fuel to spill onto the road, creating a fire hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the tank
fuel smell inside or outside the vehicle
fuel level drops rapidly
rust or corrosion visible on the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to become stuck or inoperable, which can lead to reduced visibility, increased risk of injury in the event of an emergency, and decreased overall vehicle safety.
symptoms: The window is stuck or will not move
the window regulator makes a grinding or scraping noise
the window is difficult to open or close
the window falls or drops suddenly
the window is stuck in a partially open or closed position.
